  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We note that, because these fields are countable, the rank of the Mordell-Weil groups over such a field has infinite rank if and only if it has rank ℵ 0.",
    "Theorem 4.1.",
    "Suppose that K is a finitely generated field over Q and e ≥ 2.",
    "Then, for almost all σ ∈ G e K, the following statement holds: for any finite extension L of K[σ] and any semiabelian variety A of positive dimension over L, the group A(L)/A(L) tor is a free Z-module of rank ℵ 0.",
    "Before proving this theorem, let us recall the proposition by Moon [Moo09], which plays a key role in our proof."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Before proving this theorem, let us recall the proposition by Moon [Moo09], which plays a key role in our proof."
  ]
}